Created a side project - Clone of Threads web app

A few weeks ago @_junhoyeo started an unofficial Threads API.  Since there was an easy way to get data I started building a clone.

Using Next, Tailwind, three.js, and shadcn components I threw together a clone.  This gave me a chance to dive deeper into Next’s newer app router.

https://github.com/e-roy/threads-clone

The new version of the Unofficial Threads API arrived... with a bunch of methods made possible by @🐼stevenlafl's work (he's building a web client for Threads) 🔥
Now you can query ✨full user/post details and 💎recommended accounts, 🔇mute and block users(or a specific post), 🔔 read notifications, 🔍 and search users, all though code!
Project repo her3 > https://github.com/junhoyeo/threads-api

And we have updates to our 🤖App Registry!
⭐️ @digital39999 built a 👾Discord bot that can mirror new posts from accounts in Threads (https://threadsbot.us)
⭐️ @swarajbachu made another web client that can post threads online 👏 (https://threads.aperturs.com)
Nice to see you all building 🛠️
Interesting! By the way, really awesome job on building the unofficial API! 🙌
